trend_summary: Across the time-series the city core retains its compact form while surrounding woodland is slowly replaced by new suburbs and light-industrial parks. Built-up footprint grows moderately along the highway and in the west, indicating steady but not explosive growth. Downtown roofs become larger and denser, yet extensive tree cover keeps overall character semi-suburban.
notable_changes: Progressive expansion of residential subdivisions west and north of the core.
Larger, denser roofing footprints in the central business district.
Conversion of several industrial/warehouse parcels to mixed commercial uses.
Noticeable reduction of tree cover immediately flanking the main highway.
